                            <comment id="12767451" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 18:56:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes the mentioned problem, passes tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767459" author="streamy" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 19:12:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good, JD.  +1 for commit to branch and trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767493" author="stack" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 19:53:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 but mildly interested in what happens if no port on the serverAddress...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need an issue for fact that on each heartbeat, a dns lookup is also done.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12767503" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 20:03:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks guys for looking at the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Stack, here&apos;s the code in HSA that was called:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; colonIndex = hostAndPort.lastIndexOf(&apos;:&apos;);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;(colonIndex &amp;lt; 0) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IllegalArgumentException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Not a host:port pair: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + hostAndPort);
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; host = hostAndPort.substring(0, colonIndex);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; port =
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;.valueOf(hostAndPort.substring(colonIndex + 1)).intValue();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At first I tried to put it in a helper method but the code is so simple I could just copy it over so we&apos;ll have the same behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767515" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 20:23:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Something like this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767534" author="streamy" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 20:49:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for commit, does not change behavior and resolves issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767560" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 21:30:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767636" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2009 00:40:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well it seems that some resolving is needed. From some debug I added: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
